# DIG Browser branding (product/company names).
#
# Rebrands the unbranded Chromium product as the "DIG Browser" (a DIG Network
# product) at its single source of truth: the chromium-channel BRANDING file,
# which feeds the installer, the About box, Windows shortcuts and VERSIONINFO.
# Strings only — no behavioural change to the upstream ungoogled-chromium
# patches. Icons, theme color and the new-tab page are applied by the
# companion windows-dig-newtab.patch and the build harness
# (build.py:_apply_dig_branding).
#
# The six product/company lines below are the first six lines of the BRANDING
# file and are stable across Chromium releases, so this hunk applies cleanly.
# The user-visible IDS_PRODUCT_NAME / IDS_SHORTCUT_NAME /
# IDS_ABOUT_VERSION_COMPANY_NAME strings in chromium_strings.grd are rebranded
# by build.py:_apply_dig_branding (a tolerant text substitution that does not
# depend on exact line numbers), keeping this patch robust across rebases.

--- a/chrome/app/theme/chromium/BRANDING
+++ b/chrome/app/theme/chromium/BRANDING
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
-COMPANY_FULLNAME=The Chromium Authors
-COMPANY_SHORTNAME=The Chromium Authors
-PRODUCT_FULLNAME=Chromium
-PRODUCT_SHORTNAME=Chromium
-PRODUCT_INSTALLER_FULLNAME=Chromium Installer
-PRODUCT_INSTALLER_SHORTNAME=Chromium Installer
+COMPANY_FULLNAME=DIG Network
+COMPANY_SHORTNAME=DIG Network
+PRODUCT_FULLNAME=DIG Browser
+PRODUCT_SHORTNAME=DIG Browser
+PRODUCT_INSTALLER_FULLNAME=DIG Browser Installer
+PRODUCT_INSTALLER_SHORTNAME=DIG Browser Installer
